title: For Sale/Trade:  1,000 rounds Federal XM193BK 5.56X45 mm 55 GR. MCBT BALL
postcontent:
As the title says.  This is a sealed box of 1,000 rounds, I will not break it up, or even open it.  Price is .70 cents a round.  Pick up is in Jacksonville, NC, near the newer WalMart only, absoloutely no shipping.   If you don't like my price, you have two choices, make me a good offer on it, or buy it from someone else if you can find it, but don't email to complain about it, it is that simple.

I've just completed selling my magazines on gunbroker.com, and this is all the ammo I have left that I want to sell, but I don't need to.  My price is reflective of what bidders are pricing the value of this ammo at auction on GB, so that is why I have no problem in asking this much, supply and demand is the rule of the day, and I'm going with the flow.

FYI, I sold my magazines on GB, 110 of them, both new and used, USGI and PMAGs, and my starting price for new mags was the same as an internet retailer would sell them for.  The average price of the magazines I sold was driven up to 28.09, by the bidders, so before you begin complaining about the price you are paying for ammo, magazines, rifles, etc., take a look around at all the folks buying in a panic, depleteing the supply chain, driving the prices up through the roof.  Before you complain about the sellers and their asking prices, realize that they are simply eliminating the long wait for an auction to end, at a price that is ridiculous, by pricing their items at what they are worth right now, and would likely be bought by someone to resell for a higher price anyway.  Think about it, it isn't confusing.  My personal opinion is this, the panic on the rifles and magazines may be warranted, but I don't believe it is on the ammo, in fact, I'm almost positive.  That being said, I am more than willing to make a profit on the ammo I worked hard for, to purchase when I could afford it, so that I can make money to buy the things I need that I can not afford at the moment.

Have a great day, and a Happy New Year!  
Semper Fi

title: For Sale:  latest production 41 Rimfire Short Remington Derringer
postcontent: I have a prestine remington 41 Rimfire short over and under derringer that was my grandfathers. This Derringer looks as though it was never fired and handled very little. I would rate it at 98% condidtion. It also comes with a complete unbroken (full) box of Navy Arms 41 Rimfire short that is extreemly hard to find. The Remington UMC Derringer .41 RF caliber derringer. Remington Over/Under Derringer with Monoblock barrels. This is a later production gun where approximately 500 or so of these guns were made with the monoblock barrels. These guns have an hour glass profile to the barrels while the earlier guns have a rib milled in the between the barrels which gives the profile of two barrels attached together like a shotgun. The one I have is SN 1533, assuming Remington started the SN of this model at 1000, this could very well be the last one of these fine derringers that Remington ever made. $4500 is Firm. This is a very sought after collectable. The only reason I am considering letting it go is because I have decided to stick with items I can "fire". If you are interested please E-mail me.
